And so, this is going to
be equal to the vector

00:04:06.136 --> 00:04:09.906
negative two comma negative four.

00:04:09.906 --> 00:04:11.348
Well, let's plot that.

00:04:11.348 --> 00:04:12.914
The x component is negative two.

00:04:12.914 --> 00:04:15.414
So it's negative one, negative two.

00:04:15.414 --> 00:04:16.604
And the y component,

00:04:16.604 --> 00:04:19.529
negative one, two,

00:04:19.529 --> 00:04:22.312
three, I'm going a little
bit off of my axes,

00:04:22.312 --> 00:04:24.528
four, so that would be
negative four there,

00:04:24.528 --> 00:04:25.929
that's negative two.

00:04:25.929 --> 00:04:28.584
So it's going to look something like this.

00:04:28.584 --> 00:04:32.958
It's going to look something like,

00:04:32.958 --> 00:04:35.470
something like that.

00:04:35.871 --> 00:04:37.166
So that right over there is the vector

00:04:37.166 --> 00:04:39.501
negative two w.

00:04:39.501 --> 00:04:41.370
Now let's think about what just happened.

00:04:41.370 --> 00:04:44.377
Well, because we had the negative here,

00:04:44.377 --> 00:04:47.458
it essentially flipped in
