00:05:08.415 --> 00:05:09.614
of our original vector,

00:05:09.614 --> 00:05:11.301
and it's going in the opposite direction

00:05:11.301 --> 00:05:13.088
because of the negative sign.

00:05:13.088 --> 00:05:14.694
So hopefully this gives you
a little bit on intuition

00:05:14.694 --> 00:05:17.334
of what it means to scale a vector.

00:05:17.334 --> 00:05:20.145
And literally, the word scalar,

00:05:21.005 --> 00:05:22.401
let me write it down.

00:05:23.201 --> 00:05:24.961
Scalar.

00:05:24.961 --> 00:05:26.465
That's a scalar, that's a scalar.

00:05:26.465 --> 00:05:27.968
It has the word scale in it.

00:05:27.968 --> 00:05:30.447
It's literally just scaling the vector.

00:05:30.447 --> 00:05:32.621
It is changing its magnitude.

00:05:32.621 --> 00:05:34.957
It might flip it around
because of a negative sign,

00:05:34.957 --> 00:05:37.070
